key_cycle_8_discoveries: DISCOVERY 1: The Financial Services Cascade is CONFIRMED and ACCELERATING. BLS shows accounting employment down 49K YoY, FRED shows rising business loan delinquency (1.78%), YFinance shows financials dead last among sector ETFs (+0.5%). This is not a prediction — it is HAPPENING. All financial/accounting models upgraded.

DISCOVERY 2: Staffing Industry Destruction is the STRONGEST MARKET SIGNAL in the dataset. Three major staffing stocks down 25-53% in one year while the broad market is up. This EXCEEDS the signal strength of the accounting cascade. Staffing models jumped from ranks 21/35 to ranks 13/20.

DISCOVERY 3: Physical production sectors CONFIRMED by market momentum. Industrials (+15.1%), Materials (+20.1%) are among the top-performing sector ETFs. This validates the physical production / acquire-and-modernize thesis with real-time capital flow data. Manufacturing models maintain top rankings.

DISCOVERY 4: Zero-density gaps VALIDATED. Web search confirms ZERO funded AI startups in wholesale distribution, commercial printing, and specialty food production. These are the deepest Schumpeterian gaps — strong structural forces but literally no AI entrepreneurs have noticed them.

DISCOVERY 5: Auto repair is NO LONGER zero-density. Revv raised $20M specifically for AI auto repair. This is a significant competitive signal that emerged between pre-cycle 8 and cycle 8. Auto repair models downgraded.

DISCOVERY 6: AI infrastructure capex may be peaking. NVIDIA flat (+3.7%), Microsoft DOWN (-23.6%) in 6 months. Kondratieff deployment phase transition: infrastructure buildout → application deployment. This is GOOD for application-layer businesses (our models).

DISCOVERY 7: Business formation remains strong (532K applications/month) despite rising delinquency. This confirms Coasean shrinkage: old businesses dying, new micro-firms forming. Validates demand for AI-powered business services infrastructure.
